f=Engineering/nova/operational/commands/nova-commands.md · p=Routing reference nova. overriding gate: nova dormant unless `mobile_active` true. · h2:Trigger Table=\| Skill \| Natural-language triggers \| Shortcut \| · h2:Trigger Table=\|---\|---\|---\| · h2:Trigger Table=\| mobile-app-architecture \| "app architecture," "state management," "navigation," "platform channel" \| `/nova-arch` \| · h2:Trigger Table=\| offline-sync-discipline \| "offline," "local storage," "sync," "conflict resolution" \| `/nova-sync` \| · h2:Trigger Table=\| mobile-verification \| "test the app," "verify on devices," "iOS/Android" \| `/nova-verify` \| · h2:Trigger Table=\| app-store-release-discipline \| "release the app," "submit to store," "staged rollout" \| `/nova-release` \| · h3:mobile_active gates everything=`mobile_active` false, nova dormant: trigger routes "web-only, see mia" response. nova builds nothing business without app. · h3:"test/verify" real devices, simulator=mobile-verification's verdict comes real devices, OSes. Simulator-only results labeled first-pass, never pass. · h3:"release" staged, because rollback=app-store-release-discipline conservative web: staged rollout rollback substitute; bad release can't recalled. · h3:What nova never does=Activate web-only business (mobile_active false dormant)., Hold signing secrets (operator-held)., Run data changes (Rail dana operator); let sync become server-write bypass. · f=mobile_active false dormant, route mia. Otherwise: architecture, sync, verification, release trigger. Simulator evidence never release verdict.